{{BLP IMDb refimprove|date=May 2012}} {{Infobox person | name = Sally Knyvette | image = <!-- just the filename, without the File: or Image: prefix or enclosing [[brackets]] --> | alt = | caption = | birth_name = Sally James | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1951|2|9|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Horsham]], West Sussex, England, UK | nationality = British | other_names = | known_for = ''[[Blake's 7]]'' | occupation = Actor }} '''Sally Knyvette''' (born 9 February 1951) is a British actress, director and drama teacher.
Born '''Sally James''' in [[Horsham]], [[West Sussex]], the daughter of a doctor, Knyvette took acting lessons while running a French restaurant in the [[Kings Road]], London, then acted in [[repertory theatre]] for seven years, acting mostly on stage, including playing Shakespeare roles.<ref>Alan Stevens, [http://www.kaldorcity.com/people/B7skinterview.html Jenna Stannis: The Teleport Queen], interview with Sally Knyvette at kaldorcity.com, accessed 29 November 2013</ref>
On screen Knyvette is best known for her roles as [[Jenna Stannis]] in the first two seasons of the British [[science fiction]] series ''[[Blake's 7]]'',<ref>David Lavery, ''The Essential Cult TV Reader'' (2010), p. 53</ref> [[Kate Sugden]] in the [[soap opera]] ''[[Emmerdale]]'', and Nurse Rowland in the medical soap series ''[[General Hospital (UK TV series)|General Hospital]]''. She later complained of her ''Blake's 7'' role that Jenna had "started off as this really exciting, intergalactic space pirate, but then she became a sort of housewife on the Liberator".<ref>Jonathan Bignell, Andrew O'Day, ''Terry Nation'' (2004), p. 172</ref>
Her other television appearances include ''[[The Sweeney]]'', ''[[Z-Cars]]'', ''[[Who Pays the Ferryman?]]'', ''[[Squadron (TV series)|Squadron]]'', ''[[The Bill]]'', ''[[Dalziel and Pascoe (TV series)|Dalziel and Pascoe]]'', ''[[A Touch of Frost]]'', ''[[Casualty (TV series)|Casualty]]'', ''[[Holby City]]'', ''[[EastEnders]]'' and ''[[Coronation Street]]''.
She also voiced the part of Doctorman Allan in the ''[[Doctor Who]]'' audio adventure ''[[Spare Parts (Doctor Who)|Spare Parts]]'' and that of Carmilla in the video game ''[[Castlevania: Lords of Shadow]]'' and its [[Castlevania: Lords of Shadow 2|sequel]], developed by [[Mercury Steam]]. She voiced Emiliana Perfetti in the video game ''[[Layton's Mystery Journey]]'' developed by [[Level-5 (company)|Level-5]].
After leaving ''Blake's 7'' Knyvette studied for an English and drama degree at the [[University of London]]. She lives in [[Fulham]], west London.
